                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>\n                                        <date>June 27/51</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dr Sir Your favor<lb/> of <date>10th</date> inst\n                                        has been some time received.<lb/> I have been obliged to\n                                        leave town for<lb/> some days since it reached me, or I\n                                        would<lb/> have received my earlier attention. I<lb/> have\n                                        collected $9 from <persName>A Moise Inn</persName>\n                                        &amp;<lb/> will send to <persName>Mrs Griswold</persName>\n                                        for the amt<lb/> due from her. <persName>Mr Joshua\n                                                  Lazarus</persName> as<lb/> you are doubtless aware\n                                        has left for<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>Europe</placeName>. I ascertain thus far that<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mrs M L Cohen</persName><lb/>     <persName>John\n                                                  I. Cohen</persName><lb/>     <persName>Leopold\n                                                  Cohn</persName><lb/>\n                                        <persName>Col M Jacobs</persName><lb/> are <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">not</hi> subscribers to the\n                                        Occident. My<lb/> friend <persName>P Wineman</persName> did\n                                        not desire it<lb/> either, but (to please me I think)\n                                        has<lb/> concluded to take it for the year at<lb/> any rate.\n                                                  <persName>Mr B D\n                                        Lazarus</persName><lb/>               &amp; <persName>B\n                                                  Mordecai</persName><lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">marked with a star</hi> in yr list, I\n                                        have<lb/> not yet seen. I have not had time<lb/> to solicit\n                                        new subscribers, but yr list<lb/> is so full already in\n                                                  <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, that<lb/> I\n                                        know of few others to whom<lb/> application could be made.\n                                        In the</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm0j/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
