                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>cases of the 4 persons before named who<lb/> decline the Occident,\n                                        I have not been<lb/> able to get numbers back. Some say<lb/>\n                                        they did not get but <hi rend=\"underline\">one</hi>\n                                        number,<lb/> &amp; others that what they did get were<lb/>\n                                                  ret<hi rend=\"underline\">d</hi> &amp;c &amp;c I\n                                        will endeavor to <hi rend=\"underline\">retain</hi><lb/>\n                                        <persName>B Mordecai</persName> &amp; <persName>B D\n                                                  Lazarus</persName> if possible<lb/> I learn from\n                                                  <persName>David Lopez</persName>, <persName>M H\n                                                  Nathan</persName><lb/>\n                                        <persName>M D Hyams</persName> &amp; <persName>N A\n                                                  Cohen</persName> that their<lb/> withdrawal from\n                                        yr subscription roll<lb/> originated from no objection to yr\n                                        course<lb/> The two first did not want it &amp; had<lb/> no\n                                        time to read it &amp; the two last had<lb/> copies in their\n                                        houses taken by their<lb/> sons. I will inquire of\n                                                  <persName>Jackson Moses</persName><lb/> whether he\n                                        considers himself a subscriber<lb/> or, also of <persName>I.\n                                                  L. DeLange</persName> &amp; <persName>J.\n                                                  Harris</persName></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">If anything can be done for the<lb/> Prayers &amp;\n                                        Bible or Occident, I will<lb/> endeavor to accomplish it\n                                        during<lb/> the ensuing dull season.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Yr Occident for <date>July</date> is at hand<lb/>\n                                        It bears down manfully upon the<lb/> disorganizing clique\n                                        who now rule<lb/> our congregational matters without<lb/>\n                                        religion, without order &amp; without<lb/> law.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">It must do the Occident good with</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm0j/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
